Eval corpora — public domain
=============================

All texts under evals/corpora/ are RENAMED DERIVATIVES of works that are in the
public domain in the United States (each first published before 1929). See each
book's PROVENANCE.md for the source work, author, and year.

The underlying source texts are used either from Standard Ebooks (dedicated to
the public domain via the CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication) or from
Project Gutenberg with the Project Gutenberg header, license, and trademark
references stripped (per the Project Gutenberg License, the remaining text is
"unrestricted by U.S. intellectual property law").

To the extent this project holds any rights in the renaming/derivation, they are
dedicated to the public domain under CC0 1.0:
https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/

The character/place renaming exists solely to prevent train-set memorization from
contaminating the evaluation; provenance of every source work is documented, not
obscured.
